interfaces.Rule
public class Seeds
extends interfaces.RuleAbstract

Author:
Gautham Nagaraju, Prakhar Dubey, Akash Kulkarni, Victor Dong The class implements the rules associated the Seeds automaton. It consists of infinite two-dimensional grid of cells, each of which may be in one of two states: on or off. Each cell is considered to have eight neighbors (Moore neighborhood). In each time step, a cell turns on or is "born" if it was off or "dead" but had exactly two neighbors that were on; all other cells turn off.
